Sentencas: The present work is intended to study mixed conductivity of complex perovskite oxide of chemical formula Dy0.5-xBaxSr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (DBSCF-x) (0 <= x <= 0.07) to check its suitability as cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Complex Perovskite system Dy0.5-xBaxSr0.5Co0.80Fe0.20O3-δ: As cathode for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Low-temperature sol-gel combustion route has been used to prepare DBSCF-x systems.
Titulo: Complex Perovskite system Dy0.5-xBaxSr0.5Co0.80Fe0.20O3-δ: As cathode for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Structures are confirmed by X-ray diffraction (XRD), exhibit single-phase perovskite structures with orthorhombic symmetry (space group Pbnm) for all compositions.
Titulo: Complex Perovskite system Dy0.5-xBaxSr0.5Co0.80Fe0.20O3-δ: As cathode for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Thermogravimetry (TG) results indicate lattice oxygen loss in Ba-doped DBSCF system by heat treatment in temperature interval 50-850 degrees C, which is enhanced in N-2 atmosphere then air; in contrast to that lattice oxygen, gain is observed for DBSCF-0 system.
Titulo: Complex Perovskite system Dy0.5-xBaxSr0.5Co0.80Fe0.20O3-δ: As cathode for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Temperature profile of DC conductivity exhibits metallic behavior of DBSCF-x system; however, the DBSCF-0 system shows semiconductor-to-metal transition at temperature around 450 degrees C. DBSCF-0.03 system displays maximum electronic conductivity.
Titulo: Complex Perovskite system Dy0.5-xBaxSr0.5Co0.80Fe0.20O3-δ: As cathode for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Electrochemical performance of electrodes is studied in three-layer symmetrical cell configuration DBSCF-x/Ce0.85Sm0.15O2-delta/DBSCF-x by complex impedance spectroscopy (CIS).
Titulo: Complex Perovskite system Dy0.5-xBaxSr0.5Co0.80Fe0.20O3-δ: As cathode for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Impedance diagram reveals the presence of three processes mainly associated with (a) diffusion of oxide ions/oxygen intermediates through electrode/electrolyte interface, (b) atomic oxygen diffusion within the electrode, and (c) oxide ion diffusion in the crystal lattice.
Titulo: Complex Perovskite system Dy0.5-xBaxSr0.5Co0.80Fe0.20O3-δ: As cathode for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: ASR of the DBSCF-0.05 system is found 2.21 ohm cm(2) at 700 degrees C, which is lowest amongst all studied compositions.
Titulo: Complex Perovskite system Dy0.5-xBaxSr0.5Co0.80Fe0.20O3-δ: As cathode for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Results show that it is possible to modify the electrochemical properties of the DBSCF-x system by changing the composition, but much more work even including optimization of layer thickness and microstructure will be needed to reduce the ASR to the level of the state-of-art-electrodes and thereby better utilize the potential of the DBSCF-x system.
Titulo: Complex Perovskite system Dy0.5-xBaxSr0.5Co0.80Fe0.20O3-δ: As cathode for IT-SOFCs
